<h2>Questions We Get on These Calls</h2>

<h3>My LG dryer door won't latch — why won't the dryer start?</h3>
<p>LG dryers have a door switch that cuts power to the motor when the door isn't fully closed. If the latch is broken and the door doesn't click shut, the switch never engages and the dryer won't start. Fix the latch and the dryer starts normally. Cost: $150–200.</p>

<h3>My LG dryer door makes a clicking sound when I close it but bounces back open. What's wrong?</h3>
<p>The latch tab is broken or worn — it may feel like it's catching but releases immediately. Sometimes the strike has shifted position from vibration over the years and the latch is hitting the wrong spot. We check both before recommending any parts. Sometimes it's just a strike adjustment with no parts needed.</p>

<h3>My LG dryer door is sagging and won't close properly. Is it the latch?</h3>
<p>Probably the hinge, not the latch. A sagging door means the hinge has worn and the door no longer aligns with the latch strike — the tab hits in the wrong spot. Replacing the latch won't fix a hinge alignment problem. We watch the door close to confirm which it is. Cost: $180–230 for both hinges.</p>

<h3>Do you stock LG dryer door parts on your trucks?</h3>
<p>Yes — we carry latch assemblies and hinges for the most common LG models including DLGX and DLEX series. Most door calls are done in one visit. Less common models or specific seal gaskets may require ordering, but we'll tell you when you call with your model number.</p>

<h3>Can I keep using my dryer if the door pops open mid-cycle?</h3>
<p>No — stop using it. A door that opens mid-cycle vents hot air into the laundry room and leaves the drum accessible while it may still be spinning. It's a safety issue, not just an inconvenience. The repair is straightforward and cheap — don't put it off.</p>

<h3>How long does door latch replacement take?</h3>
<p>Usually 30–45 minutes on-site — one of the faster repairs we do. We test the door multiple times before we leave and confirm the dryer starts and runs without stopping. Hinge replacement takes 45–60 minutes due to the alignment work involved.</p>

